    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f08290936">Heated Wiper Blades</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f08290936" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g08290927.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Heated Wiper Blade Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WIPER MOTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ELECTRICAL SYSTEM CONTROLLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TURN SIGNAL WIPER CONTROL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HEATED WIPER BLADE SWITCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The heated wiper blades are an independent system from the wiper system. The heated wiper blades will
                activate a heating coil to prevent ice buildup. The heated wiper blades can be activated when the wiper
                motor is on or off. To diagnose the windshield wiper motor, washer pump or wiper function switch, refer
                to the
                <hotlnk document="s08290_X08290129.xml" xrefid="x08290129">Windshield Wipers &#38; Washer Pump</hotlnk>
                section of this manual.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
